## Early game

**Tessera** on Venus (Defense, Corpus Outpost, levels 3-8) is Alloy Plate's
best early stop — Venus is one of the resource's signature planets, so drops
show up from the very first waves without needing any gear investment. Alloy
Plate only comes from in-mission pickups (not end-of-mission rewards), so a
Resource Drop Booster applies to every drop you pick up along the way.

## Mid & late game

For a geared squad, **Tuvul Commons** on the Zariman (Void Cascade, levels
50-55) is the highest-yield spot: the endless mission's enemy density keeps
containers and drops flowing continuously. If the Zariman isn't unlocked yet
or matchmaking is slow, **Gabii** on Ceres (Dark Sector Survival, Steel Path)
is a strong fallback — the wiki cites roughly 1,000 Alloy Plate every 15
minutes there with a Resource Booster running.

